<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="533" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="22.[132,776,1900,2028]" pageId="22" pageNumber="533">
ETYMOLOGY. — From the Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ortega &amp; Gofas" authorityYear="2019" box="[440,489,1977,2001]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="533" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pulex">
<emphasis box="[440,489,1977,2001]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="533">pulex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a flea, alluding to the size and gloss of the shell recalling that of a flea; used as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
